Description: Fragment of handle of a probablky Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium red-brown; mixed inclusions. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Pencil '3d' (or a). Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0443)
